1. echo - Used to display a line test/string which is passed in as an argument Syntax : 
   $echo [option] [String]

   Tags - $echo -e : it enables the echo command to recognize the backlash escape 
   sequences inside the argument

2. rm - It helps to you delete files and directories.
   $rm [option] [file]
   
   Tags - rm -i "<File name>"

3. rmdir - To delete empty directories.
   Tags  - rmdir --help
